WEBVTT



00:00:07.488 --> 00:00:14.976
I thank you for joining us this week as we observe Lent together here at Calvary and as we walk with Jesus in the time leading up to his death.

00:00:14.720 --> 00:00:15.904
on the cross.

00:00:16.480 --> 00:00:22.272
This past Sunday we spent time in Matthew 16 and we're in the city of Caesarea Philippi.

00:00:22.560 --> 00:00:32.608
One of the interesting things about Caesarea Philippi is that it was a very pagan city. So Jesus took his disciples from where they were comfortable, from where their homes were, where they had been evangelizing and speaking to

00:00:32.128 --> 00:00:35.616
Speaking to the crowds and healing and doing so many miracles.

00:00:35.424 --> 00:00:38.560
And he took them north to a city that couldn't

00:00:38.240 --> 00:00:40.640
You probably have cared less about Jesus.

00:00:40.352 --> 00:00:50.400
There were temples to Greek gods. There were so many other things that were taking place that would have made people resistant to Jesus and what he was teaching because he was

00:00:49.920 --> 00:00:54.816
Because people were trying to fulfill their desires in whatever way they saw it possible.

00:00:54.560 --> 00:00:57.600
leaving no room for what Jesus had for them.

00:00:57.920 --> 00:01:01.920
So as we think through Jesus asking his disciples what the people thought

00:01:01.664 --> 00:01:03.200
Of who he was.

00:01:03.456 --> 00:01:09.856
He's asking his followers and his friends, like, who do these people in this area think I am? They probably think I'm a nobody.

00:01:10.240 --> 00:01:16.832
I'm just somebody from down south who's got a lot of people following him around and said some crazy things on mountains.

00:01:17.408 --> 00:01:22.912
But his disciples knew the truth. So when he looked at Simon Peter and he says, "Who do you think I am?"

00:01:23.232 --> 00:01:26.752
He was quick to declare that Jesus is the Messiah.

00:01:27.200 --> 00:01:33.408
And when we think of Jesus as the Messiah, he's not just the Messiah for his disciples and those who had already started following him.

00:01:33.568 --> 00:01:40.992
He's in this city filled with people who needed to hear about him. He is their Messiah as well if they choose to follow him and trust in him.

00:01:41.312 --> 00:01:43.552
So the hope that I have in the the.

00:01:43.552 --> 00:01:48.160
The great thing about hearing this message is that Jesus came for everybody.

00:01:48.224 --> 00:01:51.072
Anybody who is willing to accept his free gift

00:01:50.944 --> 00:01:53.664
Of love and put their trust in him

00:01:53.536 --> 00:01:55.840
Can receive salvation

00:01:55.680 --> 00:01:56.928
And he

00:01:56.736 --> 00:01:58.656
is their Messiah.

00:01:58.336 --> 00:01:59.712
He is our Messiah.

00:01:59.808 --> 00:02:01.952
And we can proclaim that to everybody.

00:02:01.984 --> 00:02:11.232
So this week, as you're going about your day, whatever you have planned, whatever God has planned for you, let's be reminded that Jesus is our Messiah. He is the God who saves us.

00:02:11.072 --> 00:02:19.776
And he is the God who is still saving people, the God who loves you, and the God who wants to walk with you through this season of Lent and forward on in your journey with him.
